doc.after: Molecular biology is the study of biology at a molecular level 40 This field overlaps with other areas of biology particularly with genetics and biochemistry Molecular biology chiefly concerns itself with understanding the interactions between the various systems of a cell including the interrelationship of DNA RNA and protein synthesis and learning how these interactions are regulated
